==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thebaic
<hw>The*ba"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>thebaicus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Thebes in
Egypt; specifically, designating a version of the Bible preserved by the
Copts, and esteemed of great value by biblical scholars. This version is
also called the <xex>Sahidic version</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thebaid</ent>⟦br⟧
